'''Kifune Shrine''' (貴船神社) is a {{ill|Shrine|ja|神社|12=draft}} located in Honmachi, {{ill|Ogaki City|ja|大垣市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Gifu Prefecture|ja|岐阜県|12=draft}}. It is situated along the {{ill|Minamonogawa|ja|水門川|12=draft}} in Honmachi.

== deity ==
* {{ill|Takamori no Kami|ja|高龗神|lt=Takamori Ōkami|lt_ja=高龗大神|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Ietsu-no-miko-no-mikoto|ja|家津御子命大神|12=draft}}

== History ==
It is said that the origin dates back to when {{ill|Toda Shitetsu|ja|戸田氏鉄|12=draft}}, while serving as the lord of the {{ill|Amagasaki Domain|ja|尼崎藩|12=draft}} in {{ill|Settsu Province|ja|摂津国|12=draft}}, enshrined a branch shrine from the Kifune Shrine of {{ill|Kyoto|ja|京都|12=draft}}. Since Toda Shitetsu held lordship from {{ill|Genna Era|ja|Genna|12=draft}} 2 ({{ill|1616|ja|1616|12=draft}}) to {{ill|Kan'ei Era|ja|寛永|12=draft}} 12 ({{ill|1635|ja|1635|12=draft}}), it is presumed that the branch was established during that period.

In {{ill|Kan'ei Era|ja|寛永|12=draft}} 12 (1635), when the shrine was transferred to the {{ill|Ogaki Domain|ja|大垣藩|12=draft}} of {{ill|Mino Province|ja|美濃国|12=draft}}, it was relocated within {{ill|Ogaki Castle|ja|大垣城|12=draft}}. In addition to this shrine, the {{ill|Toda clan|ja|戸田氏|12=draft}} enshrined seven shrines—including {{ill|Kumano Shrine|ja|熊野権現|lt=Kumano Shrine|lt_ja=熊野神社|12=draft}}—inside Ogaki Castle.

Around April of {{ill|Meiji Era|ja|明治|12=draft}} 4 ({{ill|1871|ja|1871|12=draft}}), the residents of Honmachi beneath Ogaki Castle petitioned the former lord, {{ill|Toda Shitetsu|ja|戸田氏共|12=draft}}, to enshrine the Kifune Shrine and Kumano Shrine as the guardian shrines of Honmachi. In October of the same year, at the site of the former Higashisōmon Yagura on the grounds of Shana‑in (a temple said to have been founded during the {{ill|Hakuhō|ja|白鳳|zh|白鳳|ru|Хакухо|12=draft}} period by the Baekje prince monk Geumju—and abolished in {{ill|Meiji Era|ja|明治|12=draft}} 2—located in the vicinity of Shimizu-cho, Ogaki City), the two shrines were merged and enshrined under the name Kifune Shrine.

== Transportation ==
* A 10‑minute walk from {{ill|Ogaki Station|ja|大垣駅|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Tōkaidō Main Line|ja|Tōkaidō Main Line|12=draft}}, {{ill|Yoro Railway|ja|養老鉄道|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Tarumi Railway|ja|樽見鉄道|12=draft}}.

== Others ==
* Along the Minamonogawa, the Minamonogawa Promenade “Shiki no Michi” has been developed. The adjacent Kifune Plaza serves as a venue for various {{ill|Events|ja|イベント|12=draft}} and is adorned with {{ill|Illumination|ja|イルミネーション|12=draft}}.
* During the annual “Honmachi Fire Burning Festival” held every November 3, Honmachi Street becomes a {{ill|Pedestrian Paradise|ja|歩行者天国|12=draft}}, hosting events such as a {{ill|Flea Market|ja|フリーマーケット|12=draft}}.

{{Shinto stub}}
